==Detailed Show Notes==

Dan and Jordan take a break from [[Alex Jones]] to discuss an interview on Project Camelot with an alleged super soldier.<ref>[https://knowledgefight.com/research/2020/5/12/episode-431-smash-n-grab-spy-jobs Episode 431: Smash-N-Grab Spy Jobs]</ref>

Topics covered include:

*Operation Green Star doesn't appear to be a super soldier program, but is the name of [https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/386618/png-processes-suspected-illegal-workers a couple of operations] [https://postcourier.com.pg/illegal-air-guns-seized/ run by authorities] in Papua New Guinea, one [https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil-nadu/2013/aug/09/Plastic-goods-worth-Rs-5-lakh-seized-505225.html in India], and [https://www.concordia.ca/content/dam/concordia/offices/archives/docs/happening/Happening-1967-68-10.pdf a clothes drive in Montreal in 1967].
*Anthony's alleged grandfather, Kelly Johnson, [https://books.google.com/books/about/Kelly.html?id=S51fBgAAQBAJ had no children].
*The [https://www.thenewstribune.com/news/special-reports/article25855081.html News Tribune article] about NESARA and its relation to the [https://www.news-gazette.com/news/two-receive-lower-prison-sentences-in-omega-scam/article_826285bb-85ef-5812-a2fd-e4c75b187c41.html Omega Trust scam].
*Anthony's [https://boxrec.com/en/proboxer/823626 boxing] and [https://www.sherdog.com/fighter/Anthony-Zender-87210 MMA] records
